        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — mesh convergence",
        "description": "Richardson extrapolation performed on three systematically refined meshes (coarse/medium/fine). GCI < 2% for all three QoIs. Required Gradation 2; achieved Gradation 3 via formal GCI study."
      },
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the pedicle screw and rod assembly using element edge lengths of 1.0 mm, 0.6 mm, and 0.35 mm in the critical thread root region. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) was computed per Roache (1998) and found to be below 2% for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement, satisfying Gradation 3 requirements."
