        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria — material and geometry traceability",
        "description": "All material properties sourced from certified material test reports for the production Ti-6Al-4V lot; geometry from production CAD files with dimensional inspection report. Uncertainty in material modulus propagated via Monte Carlo (N=500). Required Gradation 2; achieved Gradation 3."
      },
      "rationale": "Material properties (elastic modulus, Poisson's ratio, yield strength) were sourced from certified material test reports for the specific Ti-6Al-4V production lot used in both FEA and physical test specimens, ensuring full traceability. Geometry was taken from production CAD files verified against a dimensional inspection report (CMM data on file). A Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation study (N=500 samples) quantified the sensitivity of all three QoIs to ±3% variation in elastic modulus, confirming QoI uncertainty contributions below 2%, satisfying Gradation 3."
