        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria — single ASTM F1717 loading condition",
        "description": "ASTM F1717 static compression-bending at a single load angle (10°) and single crosshead displacement rate (25 mm/min). Required Gradation 3 (multiple loading conditions); achieved Gradation 2 (single standardized condition). Shortfall addressed by offset rationale."
      },
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted exclusively under the single standardized ASTM F1717 static compression-bending condition (10° load angle, 25 mm/min crosshead rate). While this is the regulatory standard condition, it does not span the range of in vivo loading scenarios (e.g., torsion, lateral bending) that the model may eventually be used to predict. This limits test condition coverage to Gradation 2 against a Gradation 3 requirement. The shortfall is accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 is the FDA-recognized predicate condition for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions, and the COU is explicitly scoped to this standardized test configuration only."
