        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Equivalency of input parameters acceptance criteria",
        "description": "FEA boundary conditions (load angle, fixture geometry, crosshead displacement rate equivalent stiffness) matched to experimental setup parameters as documented in the test protocol. Required Gradation 2; achieved Gradation 3 via direct parameter mapping table."
      },
      "rationale": "A formal parameter mapping table was prepared cross-referencing each FEA boundary condition to the corresponding experimental setup parameter: load application angle (10° ± 0.2°), fixture block geometry (per ASTM F1717 Annex A1), crosshead displacement rate modeled as quasi-static (inertial effects < 0.1% of peak force), and grip friction coefficient estimated from surface finish measurements. All parameters were matched within stated experimental uncertainty, achieving Gradation 3."
