        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria — E/uval metric",
        "description": "Validation metric E/uval (normalized error) < 1.96 for all three QoIs across all 11 specimens, AND absolute QoI difference < 10%. Required Gradation 3; achieved Gradation 3."
      },
      "rationale": "The validation metric E/uval was computed for each of the three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) across all 11 experimental specimens. All values fell below the pre-registered threshold of 1.96, and absolute percentage differences were below 10% for all specimens and QoIs. The output comparison is therefore judged to meet Gradation 3, confirming that the FEA model reproduces experimental behavior within the stated acceptance bounds."
