        "name": "Relevance of QoIs acceptance criteria",
        "description": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the primary regulatory endpoints for ASTM F1717 pedicle screw 510(k) submissions. Required Gradation 2; achieved Gradation 3 via direct linkage to FDA guidance."
      },
      "rationale": "The three QoIs — construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement — are the primary endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA's 510(k) guidance for spinal pedicle screw systems. These QoIs are directly linked to the clinical failure mode of interest (implant fracture under cyclic loading). Their relevance to the COU is therefore direct and documented, achieving Gradation 3."
